Gtk3::FzfWidget
===============

A GTK3 widget that embeds fzf as a headless fuzzy-search engine.

DESCRIPTION

Gtk3::FzfWidget runs fzf as a background process communicating via its
HTTP API (fzf --listen). The widget provides a search entry, a filtered
list, a match counter, and OK/Close buttons.

Also included: fzfw, a command-line launcher for the widget.

PREREQUISITES

  fzf >= 0.65.0 (with --listen support)
  Perl >= 5.20
  Gtk3, Glib, IO::Pty, IO::Socket::INET, JSON::PP

INSTALLATION

  perl Build.PL
  ./Build
  ./Build test
  ./Build install

USAGE

  use Gtk3::FzfWidget ;

  my $widget = Gtk3::FzfWidget->new(
      items  => \@items,
      config => { theme => 'dark', multi => 1 },
      ) ;

  # Command line
  ls /usr/bin | fzfw --theme dark --multi

KEY BINDINGS

  Down/Up     Navigate list
  Tab         Toggle selection (multi only)
  Ctrl+O      Confirm
  Ctrl+Q      Focus search entry
  Escape      Cancel

THEMES

  normal, dark, solarized-dark, solarized-light

REPOSITORY

  https://github.com/nkh/P5-Fzf_Gtk3

